pgTitle: List of RAF aircrew in the Battle of Britain (A–C)

rows.text: Born Wellington, New Zealand, 27 February 1918. Court-martialled and dismissed from RAF, Oct 1941, possibly due to bounced cheques; died UK Jul 1962
Born Bradford, Yorkshire, 6 July 1911. Relinquished commission, Jul 1956, retaining Flt Lt; became Doctor; died 1997

||KIA 18 October 1940. Died just 250 y from Borowski, who was his wingsman. Most tragic flight of 302 squadron. Scrambled in bad weather against Messerschmitts. Four ! pilots of 302 died in just one sortie hitting the ground: Borowski, Carter, Wapniarek, Zukowski. P/O Carter probably, as Borowski, was posthumously awarded with VM.
||Born Newcastle upon Tyne 1915. Seriously WIA 28 September 1940; Died of wounds 10 November 1940 Halton Hospital.
His CdG from 1940 received in 2000. Died 24 April 2004 in Katowice, buried in Kraków.
||Born Manchester, 7 September 1915. Commissioned May 1938; relinquished commission April 1965

Born Chorley, Lancashire, 20 June 1905. Commissioned on graduation from RAF College Cranwell, December 1925; cashiered by General Court Martial for low flying, December 1930; re-joined RAFVR as NCO pilot, September 1939; re-commissioned January 1943; relinquished commission, January 1955; Also awarded Belgian Knight in the Order of Leopold. Died 24 May 1974
||MIA 6 July 1942; ADC to His Excellency the Governor General, the Earl of Athlone, from 1 August 1941 to 31 March 1942.
||KIA 10 July 1940; First Casualty of the Battle of Britain,

||MIA 20 October 1940; Blenheim P6952 shot down attacking enemy aircraft off Norwegian coast; Flt Lt G M Baird captured, Sgt D L Burton captured wounded, Copcutt missing, W/O S V Wood captured wounded.
||KIA 11 August 1940 aged 27 when he was shotdown in Hurricane P3105 in combat off Margate.
||KIA 8 October 1940 aged 21 when as a Pilot of Spitfire R6779 he was shot down in combat by BF 109s and crashed Bayfors Marshes.
KIA 20 February 1945, by then a Gp Capt, buried in Toronto, Canada.
Surviving aircrew; Retired from the RAF at the rank of Air Cdre (Born 1915)
